Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9015649943746525e-29, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 215, \"end\": 222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0132339407127848e-35, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 227, \"end\": 232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0663440505479737e-29, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tensions spilled over at full time in Bordeaux with rival players and staff clashing on the pitch and confrontations continuing down the tunnel.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 379, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Crystal Palace striker Mateta struck five minutes into the quarter-final, meeting Michael Olise's corner with a superb, near-post header.\", \"from\": 381, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 463, \"end\": 476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Olise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Olise\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Olise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Olise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That proved enough for the hosts, coached by Thierry Henry, to reach the last four, where they face Egypt.\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 565, \"end\": 578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Henry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thierry Henry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Henry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Henry\"}, {\"begin\": 620, \"end\": 625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0663440505479737e-29, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Friday's clash was the first meeting of the nations since Argentina players were recorded singing racist chants about their French counterparts as they celebrated winning the Copa America in mid-July.\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6295485374344245e-18, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 752, \"end\": 758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999866227331338, \"rank\": 9.43800874287066e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"FIFA announced it would investigate the chants, which targeted France's star striker Kylian Mbappe among others and included racist and homophobic insults.\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.716120826838409e-33, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kylian_Mbapp\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.9999999992310222, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kylian Mbappe\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kylian_Mbapp\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kylian_Mbapp\\u00e9\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Argentina team were met with hostility, the crowd loudly jeering their national anthem as the sides met for the first time since the 2022 World Cup final which the South Americans won on penalties.\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 991, \"end\": 1000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6295485374344245e-18, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Giuliano Simeone and Julian Alvarez missed chances for Javier Mascherano's Argentina, and the exit of the two-time gold medallists means the winner of men's football gold will not come from Latin America for the first time since Cameroon triumphed in Sydney in 2000.\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1190, \"end\": 1206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Simeone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Giuliano Simeone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Simeone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Simeone\"}, {\"begin\": 1245, \"end\": 1262,